{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"body":"Completion verification: PASS. All 10 acceptance criteria are met, grounded in tool output.\n\nAC1 (watermark LRU eviction by mtime, grace window, off hot path): `_gc_pass` (janitor.py:336) sorts entries by `entry_mtime`, computes `grace_floor = now - cfg.grace_seconds`, skips `in_grace and not too_cold` entries, and triggers on `free < cfg.free_watermark_bytes`. Background thread is `daemon=True` (janitor.py:397). Test `test_watermark_evicts_lru_skips_grace` verified.\n\nAC2 (secondary max-age cold-trim, own test): `too_cold = mtime < max_age_floor` (janitor.py:345) triggers eviction independently of free space. Dedicated test `test_max_age_cold_trim` with `free_bytes=10**12` confirms it.\n\nAC3 (startup sweep clears tmp/* + trash/*, reconciles byte total via one walk): `startup_sweep` (janitor.py:271ā€“281) calls `sweep_tmp` + `drain_trash` then full walk + `add_bytes(delta)`. Test `test_startup_sweep_clears_and_reconciles` verified.\n\nAC4 (byte total consistent under concurrent populate-vs-evict): `add_bytes` (cache.py:109ā€“125) holds an flock read-modify-write ā€” no TOCTOU. Concurrency test `test_byte_total_consistent_under_concurrent_populate_evict` with 4 populators + 2 evictors asserts `byte_total == walk`.\n\nAC5 (trash straggler re-drained on later pass): `_gc_pass` calls `drain_trash` at the top of every pass (janitor.py:334). Test `test_trash_straggler_redrained` verified.\n\nAC6 (rename-to-trash THEN rmtree, never in-place): `_evict` (janitor.py:166ā€“180) does `os.rename(entry, dest)` then `shutil.rmtree(dest)`. Test `test_eviction_rename_to_trash_open_reader_survives` proves open fd survives eviction via POSIX delete-on-last-close.\n\nAC7 (exclusive gc/lock): `fcntl.flock(fd, LOCK_EX | LOCK_NB)` with `GcResult(skipped=\"locked\")` on failure (janitor.py:303ā€“315); fallback atomic mkdir for non-POSIX. Test `test_gc_lock_is_exclusive` verified.\n\nAC8 (corrupt entry self-healed): `reverify_entry` (janitor.py:221ā€“250) computes content digest, evicts on mismatch, next `acquire` re-materializes. Test `test_corrupt_entry_detected_and_self_heals` verified.\n\nAC9 (tunables configurable with documented defaults): `JanitorConfig` exposes `free_watermark_bytes`, `grace_seconds`, `max_age_seconds`, `reverify_seconds`, `interval_seconds` with named DEFAULT_* constants and `from_env` resolving `REBAR_GATE_*` env > `[snapshot]` table > default. `\"snapshot\"` registered in `_RESERVED_SECTIONS` (config.py:418). Tests: defaults, env overrides, TOML table, reverify period all verified.\n\nAC10 (ADR with architecture + rejected PID+heartbeat lease): `docs/adr/0005-snapshot-cache-architecture.md` exists. D3 explicitly titles and describes \"Rejected alternative ā€” a PID + heartbeat reader lease\" (lines 50ā€“62). D5 documents the full janitor architecture. Test `test_adr_records_architecture_and_rejected_pid_lease` verified via file content assertions."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1782538451324512001,"uuid":"84b308f3-08a9-440b-970d-9250e57fd85b"}